==Korean==
===Noun===
'''무자맥질''' (''mujamaegjil, -maekjil'')
#([[潛]], [[潜]]) [[dip]]ping, [[diving]], [[duck]]ing cf. Dutch [[duiken]], German [[ducken]], [[tauchen]], Swedish [[dyka]] 

====Synonyms====
* [[잠수]] ([[潛水]], [[潜水]], ''jamsu'')

====Related terms====
* [[멱]] (''myeog, myeok'', [[沐]]) [[dip]]ping, [[bathing]] (in waters)
* [[미역]] (''miyeog, miyeok'', [[沐]]) [[dip]]ping, [[bathing]] (in waters)
* [[갈매기]] (''galmaegi'') [[gull]]
* [[머구리]] (''meoguri'') (obsolete) [[frog]], cf. Japanese  [[潜り]] ([[もぐり]], ''moguri'') "diver", Latin [[mergere]] "to dive, plunge", Portuguese [[mergulhar]] "to dive", Mongolian [[мэлхий]] (melkhii) "frog"  
* [[잠수부]] ([[潛水夫]], [[潜水夫]], ''jamsubu'') [[diver]]
* [[잠그다]] (''jamgeuda'') ([[潛]], [[潜]]) To [[dip]], [[submerge]] 

====See also====
* [[오리]] (''ori'') [[duck]] (This English noun is allegedly derived from the Germanic verb cognates  meaning "dive". Meanwhile, vice versa may be the real case.)    

